<item>
            <title>[LU-13097] sanityn test_47b: create must fail</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13097</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for S Buisson &amp;lt;sbuisson@ddn.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/f6d4f1f8-22ae-11ea-971c-52540065bddc&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/f6d4f1f8-22ae-11ea-971c-52540065bddc&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;test_47b failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;create must fail
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I am wondering if all sanityn tests 47 are robust enough in case MDT0001 is on secondary MDS. Indeed, fail_loc is set on SINGLEMDS, which means primary MDS, whereas directory is created with &apos;lfs mkdir -i 1&apos;, so on secondary MDS in the context of review-dne-zfs-part-1, that has:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;MDS 1, MDS 3 on 1st MDS;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;MDS 2, MDS 4 on 2nd MDS.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;






&lt;p&gt;VVVVVVV DO NOT REMOVE LINES BELOW, Added by Maloo for auto-association VVVVVVV&lt;br/&gt;
sanityn test_47b - create must fail&lt;/p&gt;</description>
